(4160, 5018, NULL, '122355_10100937979014332', 1, '122355', 'Bryan Lowder', NULL, 'http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_world_/2013/09/30/potential_government_shutdown_how_would_the_u_s_media_report_on_it_if_it.html', 'https://fbexternal-a.akamaihd.net/safe_image.php?d=AQArp6OuDrPDrNv5&w=154&h=154&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.slate.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fslate%2Fblogs%2Fthe_world_%2F2013%2F09%2F30%2Fpotential_government_shutdown_how_would_the_u_s_media_report_on_it_if_it%2F182532993.jpg%2F_jcr_content%2Frenditions%2Fcq5dam.web.1280.1280.jpeg', NULL, 'How Would We Report on the Government Shutdown if It Were Happening in Another Country?', 'This is the first installment of “If It Happened There,” a regular feature in which American events are described using the tropes and tone normally employed by the American media to describe events in other countries.  WASHINGTON, United States—The typical signs of state failure aren’t evident on t...', 'The powers of defamiliarization: "The capital’s rival clans find themselves at an impasse, unable to agree on a measure that will allow the American state to carry out its most basic functions. While the factions have come close to such a shutdown before, opponents of President Barack Obama’s embattled regime now appear prepared to allow the government to be shuttered over opposition to a controversial plan intended to bring the nation’s health care system in line with international standards."', 48, '2013-09-30 13:21:29', NULL, NULL),
