(4567, 5339, NULL, '574908251_10151948313653252', 0, '574908251', 'Jordana Mendelson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Word problem for the day: Boy needs additional speech therapy after school (no one doubts that). A year after being evaluated by medicaid clinic, boy is assigned an amazing (male) therapist who boy bonds with immediately (all the more miraculous because session is at 6pm across town, on what is already a long day). At second session therapist informs mom (me) that he will be unable to bill medicaid because he can''t duplicate services on boy''s IEP (mom penalized for working with amazing school team on what medicaid therapist admits is an amazing IEP). Mom should 1) revise IEP so medicaid therapist can treat 2) battle private health insurance which won''t cover because boy over 3 and condition is congenital 3) throw financial caution to the wind (while also doing 2) for the sake of sanity (and boy) and pay out-of-pocket (but pants don''t have deep financial pockets, so this could be a problem). Answer: 3! In addition to being a word problem, this is also a PSA for the beauty of medicaid reform.', 50, '2013-10-29 22:04:19', NULL, NULL),
