INSERT INTO `post_data` (`id`, `friend`, `category`, `post_id`, `seen`, `from_id`, `from_name`, `story`, `link`, `picture`, `source`, `name`, `description`, `message`, `user`, `created_time`, `chosen`, `changed`) VALUES
(4595, 5350, NULL, '593707544_10151760988357545', 1, '593707544', 'Dan S Wang', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/frank.koehn.7/posts/598919116821603', 'https://fbcdn-profile-a.akamaihd.net/hprofile-ak-ash1/369952_100001105591256_1657742748_s.jpg', NULL, 'Frank Koehn', 'Mary Burke’s campaign just died. Another rich person who ignores the pleas and cries of us rural folks – She, like Tammy Baldwin’s latest missive are just very poor attempts to duck the ramifications of taconite mining, frac sand mining, corruption, and the lobbyists who are writing bills and negating the past fifty years of Wisconsin’s strong conservation ethic. In addition, Burke and Baldwin have joined the ranks of the Republican’s that have chosen to ignore science, ignore research, ignore health concerns, and ignore rural Wisconsin’s voices. Burke and Baldwin are not better than Tom Tiffany, Bob Cowles, Luther Olsen, and the likes of Mike Ellis who have ignored the scientific reports that have expressed concerns about sulfides and asbestos. Seems that the only science these folks like is the Bobby Seitz science guy cartoon who minimizes, marginalizes, and ignores any information that might caste a disparaging view Chris Cline’s mission. Now these folks use the new laws to thwart scientific investigation. Attempts were made to keep researchers out of the Penokees. Money even bought a letter from a local attorney threatening legal action against who would enter the domain of Williams/Myers/Seitz/Cline. This fearsome foursome was informed by local DA they have no authority to keep us out of the Penokees. In fact, their Senator “Taconite” Tom Tiffany has now tried to squash local control and disarm Wisconsin’s local governments to protect the environment and public health for their constituents in townships and counties.\n\nIn the process, GTac and the Walker administration have destroyed the public’s faith in the Wisconsin legislature ability to govern, lead, and represent the people. \n\nUnfortunately the Democrats are not doing themselves any favors with the statements from Burke and Baldwin. They are in effect publishing the Democrats position on the mine – Do nothing – Say nothing! This has not worked and now has created a dilemma for Democratic candidates who are hopeful to get them elected. \n\nTammy has decided to leave us high and dry. Rather than looking for ways to do nothing, she should be hounding EPA and the Army Corps to get involved and proactive. Mary should be challenging the status quo rather than joining up. \n\nTheir inability to provide leadership has created an immense political void – The Republicans are in power and will remain in power if Burke is allowed to keep passing along bullshit. We want her to call for a repeal of AB1/SB1. This legislation is junk, supported by Republicans who are afraid of the tea baggers and their very rich friends. The legislation has led to all kinds of mischief by these fools. Recent attempts have tried to change the Managed Forest Crop Laws, impact hunting, access to trout streams, limit public access to public lands, ignore the asbestos threat, and the authority of local governments. The new age oligarchy at work – those who find it easier to bow to Wall Street  - those who have no moral courage or concern for those who will follow us.\n\nRepeal AB/SB1 – this law is flawed and is not working. And there are no changes that will be satisfactory. Repeal this legislation put the old laws back in place. Then if changes are to be made let those who were elected to govern make the changes. Honest and transparent, no more scurrying around the dark recesses of lobbyists offices or the capitol building. \n\nThe Democratic strategists who are handling Burke and Baldwin are simply out-of-touch or misguided. Their advice may work well in the back room strategy sessions – The fail miserably in the public arena.\n\nSWE’s guide to electoral success:\n\nCall for a repeal of AB/SB 1.\n\nGet over Jim Doyle – Ship him off to Florida to a community for retired and ineffective politicians\n\nServe notice that WMC, GTac,  sand frac enthusiasts should not expect nor will these folks get any special treatment. \n\nJust to be clear all candidates running for office will be asked:\n\nWill you support the REPEAL of SB/AB1? Why or why not. For the record Mary, you have failed this test miserably and your position is no different from the Republican leadership. \n\nAs the first Democrat to announce: Will you call for and support the repeal of AB/SB1?', 'If Burke is not clearly against mining we definitely need to have a primary. Vinehout needs to declare, like this weekend. ', 50, '2013-10-30 00:28:33', NULL, NULL),
